author: @ukishhven7624
text: Kraven the Hunter is a cinematic masterpiece that pushes the boundaries of action filmmaking! The actors delivered performances so raw and electrifying that they felt almost otherworldly capturing the essence of their characters with an intensity that leaves you speechless. The stunts are nothing short of jaw-dropping, a perfect symphony of danger and precision, executed with such finesse that they redefine the standard for action choreography. Every fight sequence is an adrenaline-fueled masterpiece, blending art and chaos seamlessly. The commitment and passion poured into this film by the entire cast and crew are evident in every frame. Truly, Kraven the Hunter sets a new bar for action films, leaving an unforgettable mark on the genre.

author: @ebonyofthestars
text:
I watched the movie yesterday and, while I do think that the characters had a lot of potential, the movie tried to put plot for three movies into one making it feel skittish and unfulfilling. Overall, I do like the movie (though most people seem to hate it) but it tried to do too much at once.

I believe (and that's just my opinion, do with it what you will) that the movie would've worked so much better if it just focused on either how Kraven became The Hunter OR about the conflict with Rhino. Whatever was left out could've become part two or an eventual Origins prequel. The directors and script writers could've fleshed out the conflicts much more and draw at the emotions of the audience

author: @Mindurownbusiness_unknown
text: People, actually don't listen to the reviews, I saw this recently and it's a solid action flick. It's got a lot of setup and is plot heavy at times, but the acting is all there given the script, which isn't bad to be as fair as possible. Go check this out, it's thoroughly enjoyable and supercedes Morbius in many aspects and is a massive improvement on Venom 2. The cinematography is another plus, really well shot scenes. Five to eight years ago this would have been praised, only now are fans and critics difficult to please. The actors and directors placed a lot of effort into this, it was cut post production and a handful of scenes were removed to shorten the runtime. Don‚Äôt pass on this movie, it's tailored perfectly for the big screen.

text:
I am loving Kraven's intensity. I just hope they keep the fact he is a trained hunter. You can be a proud hunter and have respect for the animal kingdom all the same. Sure, its alittle morally grey but that is Kraven. In the comics he has tended to and protected a animal. In fact he's utterly horrified seeing a hornless rhino nearlly killed by poachers.

All in all while he respects animals and loves them in a twisted way, he still wants to be the apex predator in both food chains so i hope they can find that balance.

Here‚Äôs what we know so far:

- Kraven gets his powers by hunting a lion in his usual fashion, it scratches him and the lion‚Äôs blood enters his scratch wound. So as of right now, his powers are gifted by nature in the supernatural sense. Blood meeting blood.

- His powers include animal-like strength, animal-like speed, animal-like ability to climb, ability to view the world through any animal in his aoe‚Äôs eyes and to also control/make predator animals obey as the Alpha of any pack mentality would. He only has normal durability in this verse as he is seen hiding/under stress while needing to dodge gunfire.

- Rich philanthropist is also experimenting with human/animal hybridization after knowledge of the lizard/symbiotes/morbius hits the streets. His team of researchers in the samedi, kill kraven‚Äôs mother and father.

- Kraven sets on a revenge mission, only for the man to have successfully completed this process; albeit it makes the user more of an animal/less human depending on dosage. The antagonist/final battle is rhino, with Kraven afterwards setting his sights on his classic wording ‚Äúabominations of nature.‚Äù

- Kraven will more than likely travel directly to New York after the events, as Sony has confirmed that every movie after venom is a bridge-point for their Sony verse at large.

- Sony has given confirmation through every movie installed thus far, that every member of the six and numerous side villains now reside in New York (Whether they‚Äôve been shown yet or not). Aside of Hardy‚Äôs venom as well. And in the end of venom 2, we get confirmation that spiderman is present within the Sony verse, he just hasn‚Äôt been shown directly. So Kraven is now added fully to this select as well.

- The scale of this spider-man will have to be phenomenal as it seems they‚Äôre going for a Sinister Six/Kill Peter Parker mashup. And lastly, they‚Äôve already lowkey collaborated with marvel, as we wouldn‚Äôt have got the venom 2 ending scene which technically already paired the verses through multiverse. This may very well be the project that involves all 3 spiderman as it would only be fitting to face that many villains within a movie setting.

text: I really like this Kraven trailer & I like Aaron Taylor Jones in this role, but I really wish that Marvel would not have to keep recycling actors from other MCU films to cast as characters for these new roles. You can't tell me that there aren't other fresh, up and coming or established talented actors that could have played this role? ü§∑üèΩ‚Äç‚ôÇÔ∏è (it was even kind of disappointing seeing Russell Crowe being recycled into another MCU film/character when we just saw him in Thor Love & Thunder?) Where is the next generation of physical new, young, breakout action stars that can carry a major film ??! ! (Should we be maybe checking out goofy coming of age dramatic Netflix or Amazon comedies ala modern-day versions of Risky Business to find the next Tom Cruise? Can we find the next young, smart mouthed reluctant action hero like Bruce Willis? Is there a young underdog character that we can root that can do what Stallone did for Rocky I,II & III? Will we ever give young Wesley Snipes (Blade) and young Michael Jai White (Spawn) the credit they deserve for keeping the live action comicbook based film industry alive during the 90s before 20th Century Fox's first attempt at MCU  arrived with their Spider-Man, mediocre Fantastic Four or X-Men films?
